title.narrative: Service Delivery Project (SSQH - Service de Santé de Qualité pour Haïti) - South

description.narrative: (Haiti): USAID's Health Service Delivery Project in the South (SSQH-South) provides access to, and increased utilization of, primary healthcare services at health facilities in six departments in south and central Haiti. Emphasis is placed on increasing the utilization of the MOH's integrated package of services at the primary care and community levels (particularly in rural or isolated areas). These services include pre- and post-natal care, family planning, nutrition, HIV/AIDS, TB, child health services including immunization and nutrition, sanitation and hygiene. With FY 2015 funds, the project will also provide staff training and site management support at the facility level, with an emphasis on enhancing the quality of its service delivery. The expected end result of the program is the improved health status of the Haitian population through better quality primary care and health referral networks, and more rigorous management practices at the facility and community levels.
